data.meta_description: View Zu: Werner Heisenberg, Die Bedeutung des Schönen in der exakten Naturwissenschaft by Max Ernst, sold at Maximiliana: Max Ernst from the Collection of Peter Schamoni, Online Auction on Online Auction 1 - 8 December 2021. data.text:
MAXIMILIANA: MAX ERNST FROM THE COLLECTION OF PETER SCHAMONI

33

Zu: Werner Heisenberg, Die Bedeutung des Schönen in der exakten Naturwissenschaft

left signed and numbered 'XIII/XX max ernst' lower edge

middle and right signed and numbered 'VIII/XX max ernst' lower edge

3 lithographs on Japan paper

left image 30 x 22.5 cm (11 3/4 x 8 7/8 in.); sheet 39 x 29 cm (15 3/8 x 11 3/8 in.)

middle image 30 x 22.4 cm (11 3/4 x 8 7/8 in.); sheet 38.7 x 28.5 cm (15 1/4 x 11 1/4 in.)

right image 29.6 x 22.5 cm (11 5/8 x 8 7/8 in.); sheet 38.3 x 28 cm (15 1/8 x 11 in.)

Executed in 1971, these works are number 8 (middle and right) and 13 (left) from an edition of 20 hors commerce impressions (the edition was 60 on Japan paper and 185 on Rives paper), published by Belser-Presse, Stuttgart.

Estimate

£ 600 - 800 ‡♠

Sold for £ 1,764
